<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 9:21PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTH CENTRAL BEDFORD AND SOUTH
CENTRAL BLAIR COUNTIES THROUGH 945 PM EDT...
At 920 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Hollidaysburg, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Claysburg, Queen and Woodbury.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
